Philosophy
"Everyone deserves a moment."
In our culture, even taking a deep breath can be exploited. If we're not producing something, we're "lazy" or "worthless" — as if our value lives entirely in making money, and specifically in making more money for someone else than we ourselves receive.
I reject all of that.
I think you and I and everyone — even the people who have harmed me — deserve a moment to just...be.
Since we seem to have forgotten how (I know I did), I made these apps and meditations. Some are no-conflict adventures, some are zone-out-to-zone-IN games, and some are guided meditations. None of them collect data. I am not using you.
We do better together, out of generosity and care, than we will ever do trying to hurt each other.
